I'm keeping you company.

579
00:29:09,498 --> 00:29:10,498
Hi!

580
00:29:11,667 --> 00:29:14,669
What's your name? He'll write it
on the wall. Mind your business.

581
00:29:16,296 --> 00:29:18,423
Let's go. Let's go. Let's go.

582
00:29:19,049 --> 00:29:21,050
Why do I need to meet this lady?

583
00:29:21,218 --> 00:29:23,970
Hey, now it is your problem.
Oh, thank you. Thank you.

584
00:29:24,179 --> 00:29:26,139
This is that lady I was
telling you about.

585
00:29:26,348 --> 00:29:28,933
She's gonna be a big part
of your life from now on.

586
00:29:29,184 --> 00:29:32,061
I'm scared.
What if she's not nice?

587
00:29:32,229 --> 00:29:33,646
Look.

588
00:29:34,189 --> 00:29:37,608
See these right here? These are
magic sunglasses, okay?

589
00:29:37,943 --> 00:29:40,194
If you're afraid, you put them on,
they make you invisible.

590
00:29:40,446 --> 00:29:42,196
Really? Nobody can see me?

591
00:29:42,364 --> 00:29:43,698
Put them on.

592
00:29:44,908 --> 00:29:47,660
Julian? Julian!
Hello, Julian?

593
00:29:47,828 --> 00:29:49,203
Hey, Sonny,
I'm right here.

594
00:29:49,371 --> 00:29:51,456
Oh, the glasses.
I couldn't see you.

595
00:29:51,665 --> 00:29:55,293
Now, you keep those on
and no one can notice you
until you decide they can, okay?

596
00:29:55,586 --> 00:29:56,878
Okay.
All right, let's go.

597
00:29:57,045 --> 00:29:58,754
[♪♪♪]

598
00:29:58,922 --> 00:30:01,632
Julian? Julian?
I'm still right here.

599
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:04,260
Oh, okay, all right,
the glasses.

600
00:30:05,137 --> 00:30:06,179
[DOORBELL RINGS]

601
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:09,015
SONNY: Hey.
Hi.

602
00:30:09,224 --> 00:30:10,266
Welcome back.

603
00:30:10,434 --> 00:30:12,393
Who's that?
Who's who?

604
00:30:12,561 --> 00:30:13,895
[WHISPERS]
He's invisible.

605
00:30:15,481 --> 00:30:16,606
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Can I come in?

606
00:30:16,899 --> 00:30:18,232
Sure.

607
00:30:18,901 --> 00:30:20,818
Hey, any invisible people
out here,

608
00:30:20,986 --> 00:30:23,112
feel free to come in, okay?

609
00:30:25,741 --> 00:30:29,785
Sonny, I don't really know
what's going on right now,
but we should sit down and talk...

610
00:30:29,953 --> 00:30:31,829
You know you said
I got some thinking to do?

611
00:30:31,997 --> 00:30:33,289
So I did it.

612
00:30:33,457 --> 00:30:37,293
Just because I don't have a job
doesn't mean I don't wanna
move on to the next level.

613
00:30:37,461 --> 00:30:39,837
And instead of just saying
that to you, I figured
I would show you.

614
00:30:40,005 --> 00:30:41,756
Before you say anything else,
I just want you to know...

615
00:30:41,924 --> 00:30:44,133
Look at that. He took
his sunglasses off.

616
00:30:44,301 --> 00:30:46,552
He wants you to see him.
That means he likes you.

617
00:30:47,095 --> 00:30:48,137
Julian, come here.

618
00:30:49,431 --> 00:30:50,932
Come here, pal.

619
00:30:51,225 --> 00:30:52,600
Vanessa,

620
00:30:52,768 --> 00:30:55,645
I want you to meet
Julian, my son.

621
00:30:56,772 --> 00:30:58,314
Our son. I adopted him.

622
00:30:59,775 --> 00:31:01,609
I don't know what to say.

623
00:31:01,818 --> 00:31:03,152
You don't have to
say anything.

624
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:04,362
[CLATTERING]

625
00:31:04,530 --> 00:31:05,655
Uh... Heh-heh.

626
00:31:06,782 --> 00:31:08,115
Is somebody in the bathroom?

627
00:31:09,243 --> 00:31:10,284
No.

628
00:31:10,452 --> 00:31:11,452
Why is the door shut?

629
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:12,662
I don't know.

630
00:31:12,829 --> 00:31:14,789
You don't?
Mm-mm.

631
00:31:15,749 --> 00:31:18,501
I don't know.
VANESSA: Sonny.

632
00:31:20,837 --> 00:31:22,171
I can't believe this.

633
00:31:23,131 --> 00:31:25,007
Hey. Open up.

634
00:31:25,175 --> 00:31:26,217
Sonny.

635
00:31:26,385 --> 00:31:28,469
Hello. Open the door!

636
00:31:28,637 --> 00:31:30,096
VANESSA:
Sonny.

637
00:31:30,305 --> 00:31:33,558
Is everything okay?
Oh, my God.

638
00:31:34,059 --> 00:31:36,060
Man, I'm sorry.
I was freaking out there.

639
00:31:36,270 --> 00:31:37,853
I'm Sonny.
Sid.

640
00:31:38,105 --> 00:31:42,066
Hey, Sid. I had an attack
of paranoia. I thought you
were sleeping with my girl.

641
00:31:42,276 --> 00:31:43,651
I am.

642
00:31:43,860 --> 00:31:45,611
What's that?

643
00:31:46,196 --> 00:31:47,321
I am.

644
00:31:47,573 --> 00:31:50,992
Sonny, that's what I was
trying to tell you before.
I found someone.

645
00:31:51,201 --> 00:31:53,160
This old guy?
Sid.

646
00:31:53,328 --> 00:31:55,162
He's already achieved
so much,

647
00:31:55,372 --> 00:31:58,332
and yet he's still goal-oriented
and still focused.

648
00:31:58,584 --> 00:32:00,084
And he has
a five-year plan.

649
00:32:00,294 --> 00:32:01,794
What is it? "Don't die"?

650
00:32:02,671 --> 00:32:04,547
I can't believe this shit.
We got a family now.

651
00:32:04,715 --> 00:32:06,841
I thought this is what
you wanted.

652
00:32:07,009 --> 00:32:10,845
Sonny, you surprising me with a kid
that you adopted while I was away
wasn't what I said I wanted.

653
00:32:11,013 --> 00:32:12,346
SONNY:
I did this for you.

654
00:32:12,598 --> 00:32:14,807
You wanted me
to be more responsible.

655
00:32:14,975 --> 00:32:16,475
I can't raise this kid alone.

656
00:32:16,685 --> 00:32:20,021
You know, you remind me
of my oldest grandson.
You don't think things through.

657
00:32:20,230 --> 00:32:23,107
Hey, Old Man River,
zip it or I'll break your hip.

658
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:25,401
I'd like to see you try it.
Shut up, Sid.

659
00:32:25,611 --> 00:32:28,195
How could you misconstrue
the situation so badly?

660
00:32:28,405 --> 00:32:30,114
I don't know.

661
00:32:31,033 --> 00:32:32,533
Come on.
Deep down you must've known

662
00:32:32,701 --> 00:32:33,909
this day was gonna come.

663
00:32:34,119 --> 00:32:37,663
Hey. You just made the biggest
mistake of your life, baby.

664
00:32:37,873 --> 00:32:40,041
I know you're gonna be
missing me when you got

665
00:32:40,250 --> 00:32:42,585
that big, white, wrinkly

666
00:32:42,753 --> 00:32:44,337
body on top of you,

667
00:32:44,546 --> 00:32:46,380
with his loose skin

668
00:32:46,632 --> 00:32:48,424
and old balls.

669
00:32:48,634 --> 00:32:50,259
Gross. Ugh.

670
00:32:50,636 --> 00:32:52,887
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

671
00:32:53,055 --> 00:32:54,889
[♪♪♪]

672
00:32:55,849 --> 00:32:57,767
[JULIAN SINGING]

673
00:32:57,934 --> 00:33:01,187
Excuse me. How you doing?
I'm Kevin Gerrity.

674
00:33:01,396 --> 00:33:04,190
Hey, I got an emergency
problem with this kid here.
Is Arthur Brooks around?

675
00:33:04,399 --> 00:33:05,650
Yeah, I'll go get him for you.

676
00:33:05,817 --> 00:33:09,403
Can you sit over there for a while?
Stay where I can see you.
I gotta talk to this guy.

677
00:33:09,571 --> 00:33:10,946
Mr. Gerrity?

678
00:33:11,365 --> 00:33:13,074
Hi. Arthur Brooks.
How are you?

679
00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:14,575
I need to speak with you.

680
00:33:14,785 --> 00:33:16,869
I didn't tell you to come down
to the office, did I?

681
00:33:17,079 --> 00:33:19,413
Because I was
gonna send you the final
paperwork in the mail, man.

682
00:33:19,581 --> 00:33:21,415
It's like the opposite of that.

683
00:33:21,583 --> 00:33:23,668
Look, I can't manage
this kid.

684
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:26,921
I ain't a good father.
I made a big mistake.

685
00:33:27,089 --> 00:33:29,674
Mistake?
I had a mother lined up for him,

686
00:33:29,841 --> 00:33:33,469
but she's banging
the Pepperidge Farm guy.

687
00:33:33,679 --> 00:33:35,930
The kid just won't stop
peeing and throwing up.

688
00:33:36,098 --> 00:33:38,808
He's like a cocker spaniel.
I just...

689
00:33:39,059 --> 00:33:41,310
I think he'd be better off
with his natural mother.

690
00:33:42,104 --> 00:33:44,939
Well, she passed away
last night, Mr. Gerrity.

691
00:33:45,107 --> 00:33:49,443
