to be with the natural father.
It makes sense.

693
00:33:55,409 --> 00:33:56,701
Loop.

694
00:33:57,285 --> 00:33:58,327
Pull.

695
00:33:59,287 --> 00:34:00,996
Look, if you don't wanna
take care of Julian,

696
00:34:01,164 --> 00:34:04,834
we'll take him. But I gotta tell you,
man, he's gonna have to chill
for a while in a group home.

697
00:34:05,001 --> 00:34:06,794
Group home? What is that,
like an orphanage?

698
00:34:06,962 --> 00:34:08,462
Yeah. We don't call
them that anymore.

699
00:34:08,630 --> 00:34:09,839
JULIAN:
Hey, hey!

700
00:34:10,006 --> 00:34:11,173
[♪♪♪]

701
00:34:11,341 --> 00:34:14,301
Look, I did it.
Loop, swoop and pull.

702
00:34:14,469 --> 00:34:15,511
Jeez, you did do it.

703
00:34:15,721 --> 00:34:17,138
Congratulations, kid.

704
00:34:17,305 --> 00:34:18,973
I showed him that.

705
00:34:19,141 --> 00:34:21,600
Why don't you
go back over there, okay?

706
00:34:22,352 --> 00:34:23,644
BROOKS:
I'll call the Heatherton Home...

707
00:34:23,812 --> 00:34:25,146
No, why don't we do this?

708
00:34:25,313 --> 00:34:28,774
Temporarily I'll hang on to the kid
until you find him a new family.

709
00:34:28,984 --> 00:34:32,319
Oh, I don't know, man.
I mean, I gotta watch out for
the best interest of the kid.

710
00:34:32,529 --> 00:34:34,822
You said yourself you
were a bogus dad.

711
00:34:34,990 --> 00:34:37,199
He's better off with me
than in an orphanage.

712
00:34:37,367 --> 00:34:40,202
I don't wanna put him in a home
any more than you do.

713
00:34:40,370 --> 00:34:43,247
Why don't we pretend that you didn't
even come in here today, okay?

714
00:34:43,457 --> 00:34:46,375
And I'll give you a shout
when I line up a family, all right?

715
00:34:46,543 --> 00:34:47,835
That's good. Okay.
Later.

716
00:34:48,044 --> 00:34:49,879
Just don't make me regret this.

717
00:34:50,630 --> 00:34:52,131
Where are we
going now?

718
00:34:52,340 --> 00:34:56,510
I gotta make a phone call.
Just stay right here, all right?

719
00:34:57,179 --> 00:34:59,472
[PHONE RINGS]

720
00:35:00,724 --> 00:35:01,766
Hello?

721
00:35:01,933 --> 00:35:03,434
OPERATOR:
This is a collect call from:

722
00:35:03,602 --> 00:35:04,643
SONNY:
Your baby boy.

723
00:35:04,811 --> 00:35:06,437
OPERATOR:
To accept charges, say, "Yes."

724
00:35:06,605 --> 00:35:07,688
Yeah, I'll accept.

725
00:35:07,856 --> 00:35:09,857
Hey, Dad, how's it going?
How's Florida?

726
00:35:10,192 --> 00:35:13,569
Not too bad.
Your mother got a sunburn
playing tennis yesterday.

727
00:35:13,737 --> 00:35:15,237
I got some
interesting news.

728
00:35:15,405 --> 00:35:16,822
Oh, yeah? What?

729
00:35:17,032 --> 00:35:18,741
Kind of adopted a kid.

730
00:35:18,909 --> 00:35:20,075
What the hell
are you talking about?

731
00:35:20,327 --> 00:35:23,245
I'm talking about you being
a grandfather. Congratulations.

732
00:35:23,413 --> 00:35:25,289
Who the hell would give you a kid?

733
00:35:25,499 --> 00:35:26,916
Social Services.

734
00:35:27,083 --> 00:35:29,502
You idiot. You better give
that kid back.

735
00:35:29,711 --> 00:35:31,337
His mother's...

736
00:35:31,588 --> 00:35:32,797
Hang on. Hang on.

737
00:35:33,006 --> 00:35:35,007
Go play with them
pigeons, buddy.

738
00:35:35,342 --> 00:35:38,427
I tried to give him back.
I just can't, Dad. All right?

739
00:35:38,678 --> 00:35:40,054
Look, I need your help.

740
00:35:40,222 --> 00:35:42,515
I'm in a bad way right now.
Vanessa dumped me.

741
00:35:42,682 --> 00:35:44,016
I don't know what the hell
I'm doing.

742
00:35:44,226 --> 00:35:45,935
You're damn right you don't know
what the hell you're doing.

743
00:35:46,102 --> 00:35:48,020
The kid is always around.

744
00:35:48,230 --> 00:35:50,397
The past three days,
he just never leaves me alone.

745
00:35:50,565 --> 00:35:53,859
You would think he'd want
some privacy, but he doesn't.
I'm in deep shit.

746
00:35:54,069 --> 00:35:56,821
Just give that kid back
before you ruin both your lives.

747
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:58,322
Oh, I appreciate that, Dad.

748
00:35:58,532 --> 00:36:00,616
He'd be better off living in
a dumpster than living with you.

749
00:36:00,867 --> 00:36:02,576
I'll be a better father than you!

750
00:36:02,744 --> 00:36:05,079
That's impossible! Because
all you care about is yourself!

751
00:36:05,247 --> 00:36:08,707
Yeah? No, I care about you
saving money on this phone call!

752
00:36:14,089 --> 00:36:15,422
Let's eat.

753
00:36:15,590 --> 00:36:16,841
[♪♪♪]

754
00:36:17,008 --> 00:36:18,968
SONNY:
The Vanessa thing did not work out.

755
00:36:19,219 --> 00:36:22,096
She lost her damn mind.
That wasn't your fault,
though, okay?

756
00:36:22,264 --> 00:36:23,931
JULIAN:
Okay.

757
00:36:24,558 --> 00:36:28,602
I know when you first got here
you thought you were gonna
meet your dad, but, pal,

758
00:36:28,770 --> 00:36:31,146
I gotta tell you, I don't think
that's gonna happen.

759
00:36:31,398 --> 00:36:33,774
Why?
I don't know why.

760
00:36:34,234 --> 00:36:36,944
But, buddy, real dads aren't
always that great, you know.

761
00:36:37,153 --> 00:36:39,113
I got a real dad
and the guy's out of his mind.

762
00:36:39,281 --> 00:36:43,158
He's been telling me what to do
my whole life. He never lets me
figure stuff out on my own.

763
00:36:43,368 --> 00:36:46,620
A lot of dads are like that.
That's why so many people
grow up nuts.

764
00:36:47,455 --> 00:36:48,873
Look at this guy
over here.

765
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:50,499
He was probably
a nice boy just like you.

766
00:36:50,667 --> 00:36:52,960
Then his dad messed his mind up.
Now look at him.

767
00:36:53,128 --> 00:36:54,628
Hey, buddy.
Who won the Jets game?

768
00:36:54,796 --> 00:36:55,838
Who cares?

769
00:36:56,006 --> 00:36:58,299
Let it go, pal. He can't
control you anymore.

770
00:36:58,466 --> 00:36:59,508
What are you talking about?

771
00:36:59,759 --> 00:37:02,052
You know what I'm talking about.
Yeah, you're a loser.

772
00:37:02,304 --> 00:37:04,889
You're mad at your dad,
not at me! I forgive you!

773
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:08,017
I am. I am.
I hate my father.

774
00:37:08,393 --> 00:37:12,021
See, I don't want it to be like that.
I don't wanna control you, Julian.

775
00:37:12,188 --> 00:37:13,731
You even like that name,
Julian?

776
00:37:13,899 --> 00:37:15,316
I guess.

777
00:37:15,525 --> 00:37:17,651
You guess? Well, shouldn't
you like your own name?

778
00:37:17,819 --> 00:37:20,529
Why don't you pick your name?
It's gonna be your name
the rest of your life.

779
00:37:20,697 --> 00:37:21,947
What do you want it to be?

780
00:37:24,034 --> 00:37:25,618
Frankenstein.

781
00:37:25,827 --> 00:37:29,038
Frankenstein? All right.
I can deal with that.
I'll call you Frankenstein.

782
00:37:29,289 --> 00:37:31,332
What are you doing, Frankenstein?
You gonna play in the puddle?

783
00:37:31,499 --> 00:37:34,793
Well, go ahead. Puddle it up.
From now on, you do
whatever you wanna do.

784
00:37:35,003 --> 00:37:37,338
And I'll show you some
cool shit along the way.

785
00:37:37,505 --> 00:37:39,048
That's what it's all about.

786
00:37:39,215 --> 00:37:41,050
[GARBAGE'S "WHEN I GROW UP"
PLAYING]

787
00:37:41,217 --> 00:37:43,177
SONNY:
Stay in front of it.
Don't be scared.

788
00:37:43,345 --> 00:37:45,220
Here we go.
It's coming right at you.

789
00:37:45,722 --> 00:37:46,805
Okay. All right.

790
00:37:47,015 --> 00:37:49,433
You're kind of picking your
head up, buddy. Don't do that.

791
00:37:50,936 --> 00:37:52,561
Is this okay?

792
00:37:52,729 --> 00:37:54,563
That's what you wanna wear?

793
00:37:55,523 --> 00:37:56,941
That's okay with me then.

794
00:37:57,150 --> 00:37:59,652
Good luck walking down
the street, that's all I can say.

795
00:38:01,363 --> 00:38:03,072
Way to block it.
Now stay with it.

796
00:38:03,239 --> 00:38:05,449
You're the next Willie Randolph.
Remember that.

797
00:38:06,576 --> 00:38:08,577
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

798
00:38:15,460 --> 00:38:18,337
There was this guy
Chief Jay Strongbow who
used to do a sleeper hold.

799
00:38:18,546 --> 00:38:19,755
Put your arm
under here.

800
00:38:19,965 --> 00:38:22,883
Lift this arm, okay?
Slide under and try
to lock wrists, okay?

801
00:38:23,051 --> 00:38:26,095
Lock wrists. You're gonna...
Let me show you. Watch.

802
00:38:26,346 --> 00:38:29,556
Throw him into the ropes
and he comes back and boom!

803
00:38:29,724 --> 00:38:32,059
Get him. Get him.
Lock him up. Lock him up.

804
00:38:32,268 --> 00:38:33,894
Lock wrists. Okay?

805
00:38:34,062 --> 00:38:35,938
You bring him down slow. Slow.

806
00:38:36,106 --> 00:38:37,564
Apply pressure.

807
00:38:37,774 --> 00:38:39,400
And he's going to sleep
right now.

808
00:38:42,237 --> 00:38:44,071
See, he's out.

809
00:38:46,574 --> 00:38:50,285
Nazo.

810
00:38:54,499 --> 00:38:55,624
Wake up.

811
00:39:01,631 --> 00:39:04,591
SONNY:
You'll be the only kid your age
with a slingshot, I promise.

812
00:39:05,051 --> 00:39:08,429
Go have some fun.
Shoot a few beer cans or
something like that, all right?

813
00:39:12,142 --> 00:39:13,434
You like that?

814
00:39:18,523 --> 00:39:19,982
Sonny, Sonny, come here!

815
00:39:20,150 --> 00:39:22,151
What is it? What's the matter?

816
00:39:28,074 --> 00:39:29,658
Let me have that.

817
00:39:30,744 --> 00:39:33,662
Go to your room. I think.
Or do whatever you want.

818
00:39:34,664 --> 00:39:36,832
It's gonna be fun. You nervous?

819
00:39:37,042 --> 00:39:39,293
No? You're excited, aren't you?

820
00:39:39,544 --> 00:39:42,296
Let's go. Up, up, up.

821
00:39:42,464 --> 00:39:45,549
Okay. Here comes some candy.

822
00:39:48,303 --> 00:39:50,137
Hey, how you doing?

823
00:39:50,638 --> 00:39:53,015
Happy Halloween!
We got a first-timer out here.

824
00:39:53,183 --> 00:39:55,309
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

825
00:39:57,645 --> 00:39:59,063
Do the right thing, buddy.

826
00:39:59,272 --> 00:40:01,440
We want some candy!

827
00:40:05,945 --> 00:40:08,447
Hang on right here for a second,
all right? Don't move.

828
00:40:13,495 --> 00:40:15,162
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

829
00:40:23,171 --> 00:40:24,671
Yeah, that's it.

830
00:40:26,091 --> 00:40:28,008
Yeah, CDs. You like that?

831
00:40:28,468 --> 00:40:31,887
Yeah. He's not happy.
What else you got?

832
00:40:34,099 --> 00:40:36,100
Okay, yeah, that's good.
Trick-or-treat.

833
00:40:38,394 --> 00:40:40,395
Say, "Happy Halloween."
Happy Halloween.

834
00:40:40,647 --> 00:40:42,648
Thank you.

835
00:40:42,899 --> 00:40:45,400
Next year,
be prepared, moron.

836
00:40:48,738 --> 00:40:50,364
What's with the kid
wearing a cummerbund?

837
00:40:50,615 --> 00:40:52,366
I let him wear whatever
he wants to wear.

838
00:40:52,617 --> 00:40:54,076
Those boots
are the best.
Whose are they?

839
00:40:54,244 --> 00:40:56,120
I know, right?
I think they're Kevin's.

840
00:40:56,412 --> 00:40:59,706
I'll have a hot dog with
the mustard and a knish.

841
00:40:59,874 --> 00:41:01,416
Frankenstein,
what do you want?

842
00:41:01,668 --> 00:41:03,127
Thirty packets of ketchup.

843
00:41:03,336 --> 00:41:05,712
All right. Thirty packets
of ketchup.

844
00:41:06,214 --> 00:41:07,256
Ow! Hey.

845
00:41:07,423 --> 00:41:08,632
SONNY:
Nice cut, pal.

846
00:41:10,718 --> 00:41:11,718
SONNY:
Frankenstein.

847
00:41:12,137 --> 00:41:14,221
Do that thing I taught you
the other day.

848
00:41:14,389 --> 00:41:15,597
[HAWKS]

849
00:41:20,436 --> 00:41:21,520
That's cool.

850
00:41:21,688 --> 00:41:24,439
It took him like 20 minutes
to learn that, man.
He's quick. He's smart.

851
00:41:24,649 --> 00:41:26,692
TOMMY: And he loves ketchup.
Yeah, he does.

852
00:41:26,901 --> 00:41:29,278
This is like a whole
new school of child
raising I'm doing.

853
00:41:29,529 --> 00:41:31,363
You give the kid options
instead of orders.

854
00:41:31,531 --> 00:41:32,906
You know, let him make
the right decision.

855
00:41:33,074 --> 00:41:34,366
You're a pioneer.
Thanks.

856
00:41:34,534 --> 00:41:36,410
So you two just chill out
together all day?

857
00:41:36,578 --> 00:41:38,579
Basically. Went to
the park yesterday.

858
00:41:38,746 --> 00:41:41,123
Hung out on the monkey bars.
The kid did eight chin-ups.

859
00:41:41,291 --> 00:41:43,792
Eight? I can't even do one
with these scrawny arms.

860
00:41:44,043 --> 00:41:46,170
They're not scrawny.
They're nice.

861
00:41:47,088 --> 00:41:49,256
So, Julian, what do you
wanna do tomorrow?

862
00:41:49,424 --> 00:41:51,175
I wanna go to school.

863
00:41:51,384 --> 00:41:54,803
Look at that. I don't force him,
he makes the right decision.
Way to go, kid.

864
00:41:54,971 --> 00:41:57,806
We'll enroll you on Monday, all right?
Let's just enjoy the weekend.

865
00:41:57,974 --> 00:41:59,266
Do the thing again.

866
00:41:59,434 --> 00:42:00,851
[HAWKS]

867
00:42:06,816 --> 00:42:09,693
That one touched the ground.
That one touched the ground.

868
00:42:09,903 --> 00:42:10,986
That was awesome!

869
00:42:11,237 --> 00:42:12,571
TOMMY:
Good job.

870
00:42:12,947 --> 00:42:16,074
[WISE GUYS' "OOH LA LA"
PLAYING]

871
00:42:16,242 --> 00:42:19,453
Help me! Help me!
Hey, hey, shh.

872
00:42:19,621 --> 00:42:20,621
Please help me.

873
00:42:20,788 --> 00:42:22,497
I don't know where I live.

874
00:42:22,749 --> 00:42:25,000
This isn't a big problem.
We'll just, um...

875
00:42:25,210 --> 00:42:27,419
We'll find your parents.

876
00:42:27,712 --> 00:42:29,922
What's your name?
Frankenstein.

877
00:42:30,131 --> 00:42:32,132
Frankenstein. Okay.
SONNY: There you are.

878
00:42:32,342 --> 00:42:34,468
There you are.
Are you okay, buddy?

879
00:42:35,470 --> 00:42:37,471
I turned my head for one second
and he disappeared.

880
00:42:37,639 --> 00:42:40,349
Don't you ever do that to me
again, okay? Don't do that.

881
00:42:40,934 --> 00:42:43,644
Thank you so much for being
sweet to my little boy here.

882
00:42:43,853 --> 00:42:46,521
You're welcome, Sonny.
Sonny?

883
00:42:46,814 --> 00:42:49,983
I think my sister, Corinne,
is engaged to your roommate.

884
00:42:50,151 --> 00:42:52,986
Your sister's Corinne?
That sucks.

885
00:42:53,154 --> 00:42:55,989
Yeah, I'm up from D.C.
I was at that party,

886
00:42:56,241 --> 00:42:58,325
the one where we wasted
the good surprise on you.

887
00:42:58,493 --> 00:43:00,118
Oh, yeah.
Sorry about that.

888
00:43:00,662 --> 00:43:02,371
So, what, you have a son now?

889
00:43:02,622 --> 00:43:05,499
I'm not really his dad.
I'm more of a temporary
father-figure type

890
00:43:05,750 --> 00:43:08,543
until Social Services can get
another family for him.

891
00:43:08,753 --> 00:43:10,837
At which point,
you'll have to find a new way

892
00:43:11,047 --> 00:43:13,882
to initiate conversations
with girls in the park.

893
00:43:14,133 --> 00:43:15,842
Yeah, that's correct.
Mm-hm.

894
00:43:16,511 --> 00:43:18,679
Hey! Hey!

895
00:43:19,180 --> 00:43:20,389
Good job, buddy!

896
00:43:20,765 --> 00:43:22,140
He's peeing on his own.

897
00:43:22,350 --> 00:43:23,976
Keep it flowing! That's it!

898
00:43:24,185 --> 00:43:26,270
Go! Go!

899
00:43:26,688 --> 00:43:29,273
So, um, does Corinne's
sister have a name?

900
00:43:29,774 --> 00:43:31,358
It's Layla.
Layla?

901
00:43:31,526 --> 00:43:33,402
Mm-hm.
I like your song.

902
00:43:34,362 --> 00:43:35,654
Could you do me
a big favor?

903
00:43:35,863 --> 00:43:37,281
Could you just hang out
with me tonight?

904
00:43:37,448 --> 00:43:40,200
I don't want the kid to think
he's a failure because he
couldn't get me a date.

905
00:43:40,368 --> 00:43:42,577
I really can't.
No?

906
00:43:42,745 --> 00:43:44,579
No, I just have a ton
of work to do.

907
00:43:44,789 --> 00:43:46,915
I see. Hang on a second.

908
00:43:47,083 --> 00:43:48,292
Come here.

909
00:43:49,210 --> 00:43:50,794
[WHISPERING]

910
00:43:52,380 --> 00:43:56,508
Layla, if you don't come over
to Sonny's apartment tonight,

911
00:43:56,718 --> 00:43:59,511
there's a good chance
that I'll develop a stutter.

912
00:44:01,014 --> 00:44:04,099
P-P-P-Please
don't do this to me.

913
00:44:04,726 --> 00:44:07,102
That is so cheap.
What?

914
00:44:07,312 --> 00:44:11,315
[YVONNE ELLIMAN'S
"IF I CAN'T HAVE YOU"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

915
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:16,570
So I'm working
in a tollbooth now.

916
00:44:16,738 --> 00:44:19,114
I originally wanted to be
a male model,

917
00:44:19,365 --> 00:44:22,576
but turns out I'm not
very good-looking,
so that didn't work out.

918
00:44:22,744 --> 00:44:24,244
I'm sorry
to hear that.

919
00:44:24,454 --> 00:44:26,204
I'm all right.
I'm recovering.

920
00:44:26,414 --> 00:44:29,124
This is my favorite part
of the song right here.

921
00:44:29,375 --> 00:44:31,376
[SINGS]

922
00:44:32,587 --> 00:44:34,755
Better keep it down low.
The kid's gonna wake up.

923
00:44:34,922 --> 00:44:36,798
JULIAN:
Sonny!

924
00:44:36,966 --> 00:44:38,467
Too late.

925
00:44:38,634 --> 00:44:40,761
Okay. Just hang out
a little bit, all right?

926
00:44:40,928 --> 00:44:43,722
I'll be right back.
Don't go sneaking out.

927
00:44:45,475 --> 00:44:48,769
What are you doing?
You forgot to say good night.

928
00:44:48,936 --> 00:44:50,103
What do you mean? I did?

929
00:44:50,355 --> 00:44:52,939
I can't go to sleep
until you say good night.

930
00:44:53,149 --> 00:44:55,776
I didn't know that.
I'm sorry. Good night.

931
00:44:56,277 --> 00:44:57,944
Go to sleep now,
all right?

932
00:44:58,112 --> 00:44:59,613
What'd we learn
about girls today?

933
00:44:59,781 --> 00:45:03,325
Initiating the conversation
is half the battle.

934
00:45:03,493 --> 00:45:05,786
Bingo. Now sleep, okay?

935
00:45:06,662 --> 00:45:08,955
[SONNY SNORING]

936
00:45:09,123 --> 00:45:12,125
[STYX'S "BABE"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

937
00:45:13,169 --> 00:45:16,380
I gave him NyQuil.
He should be out for the night.

938
00:45:16,798 --> 00:45:18,632
This is Styx.
Yeah.

939
00:45:18,800 --> 00:45:21,134
They've been my favorite
band since I was like 12.

940
00:45:21,302 --> 00:45:22,469
You're kidding me.

941
00:45:22,637 --> 00:45:25,389
No, no, I can't help it.
I just love them.

942
00:45:25,598 --> 00:45:27,391
My friends make fun
of me all the time.

943
00:45:27,683 --> 00:45:29,476
My friends make fun
of me all the time too.

944
00:45:29,644 --> 00:45:31,103
I've seen them like 25 times.

945
00:45:31,312 --> 00:45:34,856
Tommy Shaw, when I was 16
years old, I was at the concert,
and he actually reached down,

946
00:45:35,024 --> 00:45:36,650
grabbed my hand,
pulled me on stage.

947
00:45:36,818 --> 00:45:39,152
I got to do the robot voice
for "Mr. Roboto."

948
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:42,030
Really?
No, I made that up. I'm sorry.

949
00:45:42,198 --> 00:45:44,032
That would've been cool, right?
Yeah.

950
00:45:44,325 --> 00:45:46,201
But seriously though,
my cousin's friends
with their drummer,

951
00:45:46,411 --> 00:45:48,870
so when they come to town,
